2.2 User Stories
1.	As a bookstore owner, I want to be able to add and remove new books to my inventory so that I can keep track of my stock.

2.	As a bookstore owner, I want to be able to update the quantity of books in my inventory so that I can keep track of my stock.

3.	As a bookstore owner, I want to be able to search for books in my inventory by title, author, or publisher so that I can find specific books quickly.

4.	As a bookstore owner, I want to be able to view all the books in my inventory so that I can see what books I have in stock.

5.	As a bookstore owner, I want to be able to view which books are selling or not selling to increase sales and lower inventory cost.

6.	As a customer, I want to be able to search for books in the store by title, author, or publisher so that I can find specific books quickly.

7.	As a customer, I want to be able to view the details of each book in the store so that I can see information such as the author, title, price, and publisher.

8.	As a customer, I want to be able to add books to my cart so that I can purchase them later.

9.	As a customer, I want to be able to view my cart so that I can see what books I have added and their prices.

10.	As a customer, I want to be able to remove books from my cart so that I can change my mind about purchasing them.

11.	As a customer, I want to be able to purchase books from the store using my credit card or other payment methods.

2.3 Use Cases
1.	Add book to inventory: The bookstore owner adds a new book to their inventory by entering the book’s title, author, publisher, and quantity into the system. 
    The system responds by updating the inventory with the new book.

2.	Remove book from inventory: The bookstore owner removes a book from their inventory by selecting the book from a list and clicking “remove”. 
    The system responds by updating the inventory and removing the book.

3.	Update book quantity: The bookstore owner updates the quantity of a book in their inventory by selecting the book from a list and entering the new quantity. 
    The system responds by updating the inventory with the new quantity.

4.	Search for books: The bookstore owner searches for books in their inventory by entering a title, author, or publisher into the search bar. 
    The system responds by displaying a list of books that match the search criteria.

5.	View all books: The bookstore owner views all the books in their inventory by clicking on a button. The system responds by displaying a list of all the books in the inventory.

6.	View book details: The bookstore owner views the details of a book in their inventory by selecting the book from a list. The system responds by displaying information such as the author, title, price, and publisher.

7.	Generate inventory report: The bookstore owner generates a report on their inventory by clicking on a button. 
    The system responds by generating a report that shows how many copies of each book are in stock and how much money has been made from selling each book.

8.	Browsing and searching for books: Customers can browse through the website’s collection of books, search for specific titles, authors, or genres, 
    and filter the results based on various criteria such as price, publication date, or rating.

9.	Purchasing books: Customers can add books to their cart, view their cart, and proceed to checkout. They can also apply discount codes or gift cards if they have any.

10.	Managing account: Customers can create an account, log in, and manage their personal information such as name, email address, and payment methods. 
    They can also view their order history and track the status of their current orders.
